Bowling Score Calculator
------------------------

Calculates the score a 10 pin bowling game.

This application consists of a dynamic webpage that accurately displays the score of a bowling match.
The user can enter the Webpage and enter the scores into the text boxes in the frontend labeled first
and second for each of the two rolls in each frame.

After clicking submit, an http request is sent asynchronously to a php file serving as the backend
the backend calculates the sum and returns the sum for the current fram along with total score and
the score till that particular frame.

The data is handled by the browser, so once refreshed the scores are reset.

The app can be started by executing the shell script start.sh

Requirements
------------
Make sure the host has a working version of PHP and AngualarJS
Also npm is needed to get the dependencies
PHPUnit is needed for backend unit testing

1. First, extract the project and type npm install in the terminal to get all the dependencies
2. start the application by launching the start.sh script - ./start.sh
3. Go to the browser and go to http://localhost:8000 to view the webpage
4. Enter the scores and click submit to check the calculator

Backend: PHP
Frontend: HTML, CSS, Angular
Testing, Jasmine, Karma, PHPUnit

Tests
-----

To run the tests for Frontend
Go to the terminal and cd into the main folder
to launch karma type

$ karma start

To run the tests for Backend
Go to the terminal and cd into the tests folder
and then type

$ php phpunit.phar backend_unit.php

